members.member:
Distorts the image using a wave radiating from the center. This command is available in the Raster Pro and above toolkits.
The command applies a sinusoidal wave radiating from the specified center. The center point must be defined inside the image or inside the region, if the image has a region.
If the image has a region, the effect will be applied on the region only.
This command supports 12- and 16-bit grayscale and 48- and 64-bit color images. Support for 12- and 16-bit grayscale and 48- and 64-bit color images is available only in the Document/Medical toolkits.
This command does not support signed data images.
This command does not support 32-bit grayscale images.
For more information, refer to Introduction to Image Processing With LEADTOOLS.
For more information, refer to Applying Artistic Effects.
