Wraps the image onto a 3D plane shaped by Curve. This command is available in the Raster Pro and above toolkits.
If the image has a region, the effect will be applied on the region only.
For an example, the following figure shows an image before the effect is applied.
The following figure shows the same image after the effect has been applied.
This command supports 12- and 16-bit grayscale and 48- and 64-bit color images. Support for 12- and 16-bit grayscale and 48- and 64-bit color images is available only in the Document/Medical toolkits.
This command does not support signed data images.
This command does not support 32-bit grayscale images.
Run the on an image. Public Sub FreePlaneBendCommandExample() RasterCodecs.Startup() Dim codecs As New RasterCodecs() codecs.ThrowExceptionsOnInvalidImages = True
